  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/transportation/\" rel=\"tag\">交通相关</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/14/tesla-model-s-adapter-recall/\"><img alt=\"Tesla Model S charging\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/39237fa0ffe4c33181ba8fb9e411f449/tesla-model-s-supercharger-2013-12-27-03.jpg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n各位还记得之前 Tesla 所许的将为 Model S 用户提供改良款墙上充电器的<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/11/tesla-will-give-model-s-owners-safer-wall-charging-adapters/\">承诺</a>吗？今天他们正式<a href=\"http://www-odi.nhtsa.dot.gov/acms/cs/jaxrs/download/doc/UCM448668/RCDNN-14V006-9349.pdf\">致信 </a>NHTSA（美国国道交通安全局），宣布将为 29,222 名 Model S 初代充电器用户提供主动召回服务，希望以此来打消后者对理论上潜在着火风险的疑虑。和过去的表态一样，Tesla 强调替换计划只是「预防措施」，之前的<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/12/27/tesla-model-s-software-update-guards-against-faulty-wiring/\">软件更新</a>其实已经能通过判断输入电流变化来杜绝起火隐患了。不管怎么说，我们对他们积极解决问题的态度表示肯定，接下来，就看用户是不是都买账了。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/01/14/tesla-model-s-adapter-recall/\">Engadget</a>、<span class=\"via\"><a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/15/automobiles/citing-charging-concerns-tesla-issues-a-recall.html?_r=2&amp;gwh=768C69DF7F9E20919204C558981FF4F1&amp;gwt=pay\" target=\"_blank\">New York Times</a></span><br />\n引用来源：<span class=\"source\"><a href=\"http://www-odi.nhtsa.dot.gov/acms/cs/jaxrs/download/doc/UCM448668/RCDNN-14V006-9349.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">NHTSA (PDF)</a></span></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/14/tesla-model-s-adapter-recall/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20807939/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/01/14/tesla-model-s-adapter-recall/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
